(# SEAM Operator Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is the practical runbook for interacting with SEAM, running tests, and validating the) Tj
T*
(live stack.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. What SEAM uses) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- SQLite for canonical truth, provenance, packs, and metadata) Tj
T*
(- SQLite `vector_index` by default for local vector search) Tj
T*
(- Optional Postgres + pgvector for a real external vector database) Tj
T*
(- Configurable embedding model:) Tj
T*
(  - default local deterministic hash model) Tj
T*
(  - optional OpenAI-compatible cloud embedding provider) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Where the databases live) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- SQLite truth database: whatever you pass to `--db`) Tj
T*
(  - examples: `seam.db`, `seam_validate.db`, `seam_live.db`, `seam_demo.db`) Tj
T*
(- SQLite vector index:) Tj
T*
(  - stored inside that same SQLite file unless pgvector is enabled) Tj
T*
(- pgvector database:) Tj
T*
(  - separate Postgres container) Tj
T*
(  - local validated DSN: `postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:54329/seam`) Tj
T*
(  - container name used so far: `seam-pgvector`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Environment setup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Local deterministic baseline) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(No API key required.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db validate-stack) Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db stats) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Live cloud + pgvector path) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
($env:OPENAI_API_KEY="your-real-openai-api-key") Tj
T*
($env:SEAM_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER="openai-compatible") Tj
T*
($env:SEAM_EMBEDDING_MODEL="text-embedding-3-small") Tj
T*
($env:SEAM_PGVECTOR_DSN="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:54329/seam") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db validate-stack) Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db stats) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Start the local pgvector database) Tj
ET
endstream
