(## 6. Testing SEAM) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Run the full unit suite) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
(python -m unittest -v) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Run one specific test) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
(python -m unittest test_seam.SeamTests.test_retrieval_benchmark_uses_gold_fixtures -v) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Run a strict warning-sensitive test) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
(python -Werror::ResourceWarning -m unittest) Tj
T*
(test_seam.SeamTests.test_symbol_export_and_query_expansion) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Recommended operator test loop) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```powershell) Tj
T*
(python -m unittest -v) Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db validate-stack) Tj
T*
(python seam.py --db seam_validate.db stats) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use the local baseline when you are changing core logic and want deterministic behavior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use the cloud path when you want a stronger teacher-quality embedding baseline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
